wikipedia_page.main: Arthur de Cardonnel FitzUryan Rice, 6th Baron Dynevor (24 January 1836 – 8 June 1911), was a British peer.

link_mentions.page: Arthur de Cardonnel FitzUryan Rice, 6th Baron Dynevor

response: She was the eldest child of Francis William Rice, 5th Baron Dynevor and Harriett Ives Barker. Her younger brother was Arthur Rice, 6th Baron Dynevor. Although when she was born her father was known as Francis William Rice as he was the vicar of Fairford.
* Arthur Rice, 6th Baron Dynevor (1836–1911), British peer
